2026-03-28 05:32:13 | DEBUG    | src/search_service.py:300 | [Tavily] 原始响应: {'query': 'Philip Morris International Inc earnings revenue profit growth forecast', 'follow_up_questions': None, 'answer': None, 'images': [], 'results': [{'url': 'https://simplywall.st/stocks/us/food-beverage-tobacco/nyse-pm/philip-morris-international/future', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Future Growth - Simply Wall St', 'content': "Philip Morris International Inc.\n\nNYSE:PM Stock Report\n\nMarket Cap: US$295.5b\n\n# Philip Morris International Future Growth\n\n## Future criteria checks 2/6\n\nPhilip Morris International is forecast to grow earnings and revenue by 8.4% and 6.4% per annum respectively. EPS is expected to grow by 8.7% per annum. Return on equity is forecast to be 1315.7% in 3 years.\n\n## Key information\n\n8.4%\n\nEarnings growth rate\n\n8.66%\n\nEPS growth rate\n\n|  |  |\n --- |\n| Tobacco earnings growth | 7.6% |\n| Revenue growth rate | 6.4% |\n| Future return on equity | 1,315.67% |\n| Analyst coverage | Good |\n| Last updated | 19 Feb 2026 |\n\nGood\n\n## Recent future growth updates\n\n### Price target increased by 7.6% to US$194\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2026 [...] ## Analyst Future Growth Forecasts\n\nEarnings vs Savings Rate: PM's forecast earnings growth (8.4% per year) is above the savings rate (3.4%).\n\nEarnings vs Market: PM's earnings (8.4% per year) are forecast to grow slower than the US market (15.6% per year).\n\nHigh Growth Earnings: PM's earnings are forecast to grow, but not significantly.\n\nRevenue vs Market: PM's revenue (6.4% per year) is forecast to grow slower than the US market (10.3% per year).\n\nHigh Growth Revenue: PM's revenue (6.4% per year) is forecast to grow slower than 20% per year.\n\n## Earnings per Share Growth Forecasts\n\n## Future Return on Equity\n\nFuture ROE: PM's Return on Equity is forecast to be very high in 3 years time (1315.7%).\n\n## Discover growth companies\n\n7D\n\n1Y\n\n7D\n\n1Y\n\n7D\n\n1Y [...] | Date | Revenue | Earnings | Free Cash Flow | Cash from Op | Avg. No. Analysts |\n ---  ---  --- |\n| 12/31/2028 | 50,063 | 14,446 | 15,336 | 17,455 | 10 |\n| 12/31/2027 | 46,697 | 13,505 | 14,450 | 16,208 | 15 |\n| 12/31/2026 | 43,801 | 12,026 | N/A | 14,210 | 15 |\n| 12/31/2025 | 40,648 | 11,316 | 10,664 | 12,233 | N/A |\n| 9/30/2025 | 39,992 | 8,601 | 10,123 | 11,526 | N/A |\n| 6/30/2025 | 39,058 | 8,207 | 8,989 | 10,406 | N/A |\n| 3/31/2025 | 38,386 | 7,574 | 10,195 | 11,626 | N/A |\n| 12/31/2024 | 37,878 | 7,034 | 10,773 | 12,217 | N/A |\n| 9/30/2024 | 37,219 | 9,805 | 10,040 | 11,517 | N/A |\n| 6/30/2024 | 36,449 | 8,779 | 10,121 | 11,590 | N/A |\n| 3/31/2024 | 35,948 | 7,944 | 8,941 | 10,400 | N/A |\n| 12/31/2023 | 35,174 | 7,791 | 7,883 | 9,204 | N/A |", 'score': 0.9348309, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.morningstar.com/news/dow-jones/202602064776/philip-morris-posts-higher-4q-profit-revenue-forecasts-continued-growth', 'title': 'Philip Morris Posts Higher 4Q Profit, Revenue; Forecasts Continued ...', 'content': "Morningstar\n\n# Philip Morris Posts Higher 4Q Profit, Revenue; Forecasts Continued Growth\n\nBy Connor Hart\n\nPhilip Morris International logged higher profit and revenue in the fourth quarter, while forecasting continued growth for years to come.\n\nThe tobacco company--which sells cigarettes such as Marlboro and Parliament in overseas markets, as well as smokeless tobacco such as Zyn worldwide--posted operating income of $3.4 billion, up 3.5% from a year earlier. Earnings came in at $1.37 a share.\n\nStripping out certain one-time items, earnings were $1.70 a share. That was in line with analysts' expectations for adjusted earnings, according to FactSet.\n\nRevenue increased 6.8% to $10.36 billion, just below Wall Street views for $10.38 billion. [...] Total shipment volumes edged 0.1% higher to 193.8 billion units.\n\nChief Executive Jacek Olczak said 2025 marked the company's fifth consecutive year of volume growth, with results boosted by continued growth across its smoke-free business and operating margin expansion.\n\nFor the current quarter, the company expects adjusted earnings of $1.80 to $1.85 a share, compared with analyst views for $1.89 a share.\n\nLooking ahead, Philip Morris guided for earnings of $7.87 to $8.02 a share in 2026. On an adjusted basis, earnings are projected to come in between $8.38 and $8.53 a share. Analysts were looking for earnings of $8.01 a share, or $8.34 a share on an adjusted basis.\n\nThe forecast assumes net revenue growth of 5% to 7% for the year, as well as organic operating income growth of 7$ to 9%. [...] The company additionally disclosed its compounded annual growth targets through 2028, calling for a 6% to 8% increase for net revenues, an 8% to 10% increase for operating income, and a 9% to 11% increase for adjusted per-share earnings.\n\nWrite to Connor Hart at connor.hart@wsj.com\n\n(END) Dow Jones Newswires\n\nFebruary 06, 2026 07:53 ET (12:53 GMT)\n\nThe articles, information, and content displayed on this webpage may\ninclude materials prepared and provided by third parties. Such\nthird-party content is offered for informational purposes only and\nis not endorsed, reviewed, or verified by Morningstar.", 'score': 0.933969, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.investing.com/equities/philip-morris-intl-earnings', 'title': 'Philip Morris (PM) Earnings Date & Report - Investing.com', 'content': 'Philip Morris reported Q4 2025 EPS of $1.70, meeting expectations, with revenue of $10.4 billion slightly exceeding forecasts, though stock dipped 2.75% pre-market.\n Smoke-free products generated 41.5% of total revenues ($17B of $40B+), with shipments increasing 12.8% to 179 billion units and 27 markets exceeding 50% smoke-free revenue.\n The company achieved $1.5 billion in cost savings, with adjusted operating margin returning above 40% and operating cash flow reaching $12.2 billion.\n For 2026, Philip Morris projects 5-7% organic revenue growth, 7-9% operating income growth, and $13.5B in operating cash flow.\n CEO Jacek Olczak called 2025 \'outstanding,\' noting the company reached its three-year CAGR targets for organic operating income and currency-neutral EPS within two years. [...] Last Updated: 02/06/2026, 11:02 AM\n\nRead Full Transcript\n\nPhilip Morris investor slides for Q4/2025\n\nPhilip Morris Q4 2025 slides\n\nLast Update: Feb 06, 2026\n\nSee full investor slides\n\n## Earnings News\n\n Philip Morris reaffirms 2026 profit outlook of up to 13% growth\n\n  Investing.com -- Philip Morris on Wednesday reaffirmed its profit forecast for 2026 ahead of its Consumer Analyst Group of New...\n\n  + Investing.com\n Philip Morris shares dip as revenue falls short of expectations\n\n  Investing.com -- Philip Morris International reported second-quarter adjusted earnings that beat analyst estimates, but shares...\n\n  + Investing.com\n Philip Morris International falls as Q4 results meet expectations [...] The Philip Morris EPS (TTM) is 7.26.\n\n### When Is The Next Philip Morris Earnings Date?\n\nPhilip Morris will release its next earnings report on Apr 22, 2026.\n\n### What Is Philip Morris’s Revenue Forecasts For Upcoming Quarters?\n\nPhilip Morris’s revenue forecast is 9.91B.\n\nFind a Stock Broker\n\n1D\n\n1W\n\n1M\n\n6M\n\n1Y\n\n5Y\n\nMax\n\nUS 30")\n\n45,780.70\n\n-241.4\n\n-0.52%\n\nUS 500")\n\n6,535.40\n\n-71.1\n\n-1.08%\n\nDow Jones\n\n45,577.47\n\n-443.96\n\n-0.96%\n\nS&P 500")\n\n6,506.48\n\n-100.01\n\n-1.51%\n\nNasdaq\n\n21,647.61\n\n-443.08\n\n-2.01%\n\nS&P 500 VIX")\n\n26.78\n\n+2.72\n\n+11.31%\n\nDollar Index")\n\n99.46\n\n+0.400\n\n+0.40%\n\nCrude Oil WTI Futures")\n\n98.32\n\n+2.18\n\n+2.27%\n\nBrent Oil Futures")\n\n106.41\n\n+3.54\n\n+3.26%\n\nNatural Gas Futures")\n\n3.064\n\n-0.071\n\n-2.24%\n\nGold Futures")\n\n4,609.60\n\n-30.80\n\n-0.67%\n\nSilver Futures")\n\n69.664\n\n-1.551', 'score': 0.8989177, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.tradingview.com/news/tradingview:168c3bfea5aba:0-philip-morris-international-reports-2025-fourth-quarter-full-year-results/', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Reports 2025 Fourth-Quarter & Full-Year ...', 'content': "Future Outlook\n\n \n\nPMI provided a full-year 2026 forecast with reported diluted EPS expected to be in the range of $7.87 to $8.02. The company also set compound annual growth targets for 2026-2028, aiming for 6% to 8% net revenue growth, 8% to 10% operating income growth, and 9% to 11% adjusted diluted EPS growth, excluding currency impacts.\n\nOriginal SEC Filing: [Philip Morris International Inc. [ PM ] - 8-K - Feb. 06, 2026](\n\nDisclaimer\n\nThis is an AI-powered summary. It may contain inaccuracies. Consider verifying important information with the source. Please note this summary is solely based on documents filed with the SEC.\n\nEarningsTradingViewUS stocks\n\n## More news from TradingView [...] Get started\n\nTradingViewTradingView\n\n# Philip Morris International Reports 2025 Fourth-Quarter & Full-Year Results\n\n2 min read\n\nPM\n\nPhilip Morris International Inc. (PMI) has released its financial results for the fourth quarter and full year of 2025. The company reported significant growth in its smoke-free product (SFP) segment, contributing to overall revenue and profit increases. The report also includes forward-looking statements and growth targets for the upcoming years.\n\n \n\nFinancial Highlights [...] Financial Highlights\n\n \n\nFor the full year 2025, PMI reported a diluted EPS of $7.26, a substantial increase from $4.52 in 2024. The adjusted diluted EPS was $7.54, representing a growth of 14.8%, and 14.2% on a currency-neutral basis. Net revenues surpassed $40 billion, with the smoke-free business contributing close to $17 billion. The company's gross profit increased by 11.1% to $27.3 billion.\n\n \n\nBusiness and Operational Highlights", 'score': 0.88444936, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.investing.com/news/stock-market-news/philip-morris-forecasts-upbeat-annual-profiton-nicotine-pouch-sales-4490452', 'title': 'Philip Morris forecasts higher profits, shrugging off threats from rivals', 'content': 'It added that it expected its portfolio of smoking alternatives, built to offset revenues lost as smoking rates decline in some markets, would drive shipment volume growth with rates in the high single digit to low teens.\n\nJefferies analyst Andrei Andon-Ionita said the company’s new targets provide a "reassuring outlook" on future growth, but BAT remained well-positioned to win market share in U.S. nicotine pouches.\n\nPhilip Morris expects full-year adjusted earnings per share of $8.38 to $8.53 for 2026, higher than analysts’ estimate of $8.33, according to data compiled by LSEG.\n\n## Should you be buying PM right now? [...] # Philip Morris forecasts higher profits, shrugging off threats from rivals\n\nBy\n\nStock Markets\n\nPublished 02/06/2026, 08:10 AM\n\nUpdated 02/06/2026, 12:12 PM\n\nPhilip Morris forecasts higher profits, shrugging off threats from rivals\n\nView all comments (0)0\n\n&copy; Reuters.\n\n© Reuters.\n\nPM0.43%\n\nBTI-0.28%\n\nBy Angela Christy M and Emma Rumney\n\nBENGALURU/LONDON, Feb 6 (Reuters) - Philip Morris International forecast higher-than-expected 2026 profit on Friday, even as some investors worry its leading nicotine pouch brand Zyn could struggle to fend off competitors eating into its market share. [...] The world’s largest tobacco company by market capitalisation, which sells Marlboro outside the U.S., said it expects to grow adjusted earnings per share by 11.1% to 13.1% this year, beating analyst estimates.\n\nHowever, shares in the company fell in pre-market and early trading, before recovering to stand 2% higher by 1621 GMT.\n\nPMI investors have been rattled by a growing threat from rivals, including British American Tobacco, which is capturing a larger share of category growth, raising concerns about Zyn’s momentum.\n\nCEO Jacek Olczak told Reuters in an interview that factors that make rival products more popular today may not be long-term trends, and in any case PMI was ready to launch updated versions of Zyn to better compete, pending regulatory licences.', 'score': 0.8458536, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://simplywall.st/stocks/us/food-beverage-tobacco/nyse-pm/philip-morris-international/past', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Past Earnings Performance - Simply Wall St', 'content': "Philip Morris International Inc.\n\nNYSE:PM Stock Report\n\nMarket Cap: US$253.9b\n\n# Philip Morris International Past Earnings Performance\n\n## Past criteria checks 5/6\n\nPhilip Morris International has been growing earnings at an average annual rate of 0.2%, while the Tobacco industry saw earnings growing at 5.9% annually. Revenues have been growing at an average rate of 6.8% per year.\n\n## Key information\n\n0.17%\n\nEarnings growth rate\n\n0.20%\n\nEPS growth rate\n\n|  |  |\n --- |\n| Tobacco Industry Growth | 18.08% |\n| Revenue growth rate | 6.85% |\n| Return on equity | n/a |\n| Net Margin | 27.84% |\n| Next Earnings Update | 22 Apr 2026 |\n\n## Recent past performance updates\n\n### Full year 2025 earnings: EPS misses analyst expectations [...] ### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Forecast for Full Year 2025\n\n### Is There An Opportunity With Philip Morris International Inc.'s (NYSE:PM) 28% Undervaluation?\n\nIs There An Opportunity With Philip Morris International Inc.'s (NYSE:PM) 28% Undervaluation?\n\n### Philip Morris International's (NYSE:PM) Returns On Capital Not Reflecting Well On The Business\n\nPhilip Morris International's (NYSE:PM) Returns On Capital Not Reflecting Well On The Business\n\n### Philip Morris Torches Analyst Estimates, Attractive Long-Term Upside Ahead\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Just Recorded A 9.1% EPS Beat: Here's What Analysts Are Forecasting Next\n\nPhilip Morris International Inc. Just Recorded A 9.1% EPS Beat: He